In the DID regression analysis, Ansan Danwon showed a significantly greater increase in the prescription rate of antidepressants compared to Cheonan city following the Sewol Ferry disaster (difference of 5.6%, P=0.003;
Table 2 and
Fig. 2). Ansan Danwon showed a non-significant trend of a greater increase in the prescription rate of sedative/hypnotics compared to Cheonan city after the disaster (difference of 6.9%, P=0.086). Finally, there was no significant difference in changes in the prescription rates of anxiolytics between Ansan Danwon and Cheonan city after the disaster (P>0.1).
